In many cases, users do not (know to) call _set_steps_per_run(), and therefore leave it at the default value. This results in unexpectedly skipped checkpoints. The high default value prevents this from happening at a cost of performance overhead.

If the user does call _set_steps_per_run(), this CL is no op.

Also: remove a workaround that is no longer necessary.
